<% content_for :title, "Mock — retire & celebrate" %>

<div class="mb-6 rounded-md border border-dashed border-amber-300 bg-amber-50 px-3 py-2 text-xs text-amber-800 dark:border-amber-700 dark:bg-amber-950/30 dark:text-amber-200">
  <span class="font-semibold">Mock — stub data.</span>
  The moment a word is genuinely mastered (FSRS predicts ~6-month recall), it
  leaves the rotation and we mark it. Does not touch the live drill. Sample words
  are illustrative.
</div>

<h1 class="mb-1 text-lg font-semibold">Retire &amp; celebrate</h1>
<p class="mb-10 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
  FSRS keeps stretching intervals forever; it never says "you've got this." That
  empty space is the moment we fill — quietly grander than the everyday "owned"
  pop, then the word lands somewhere it can be seen, not just vanishes.
</p>

<%# ============================================================ %>
<%# 1. THE MOMENT — the celebration overlay, replayable                 %>
<%# ============================================================ %>
<section data-controller="retire-mock" class="mb-14">
  <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-400">The moment</p>

  <%# A drill card mid-reveal, with the retire celebration over it. Same card
      chrome as the real drill; the overlay is the new piece. %>
  <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 px-6 pb-10 pt-12 text-center dark:border-gray-800">
    <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-400">Dutch → English</p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl"><%= @sample[:just_retired][:word] %></p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">✓ correct</p>
    <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400"><%= @sample[:just_retired][:gloss] %></p>

    <%# The retire overlay. Hidden until replayed. Centered card, not the small
        top pill — this is a bigger milestone than "owned". Still emerald, still
        type-led; no confetti, no loud fill. %>
    <div data-retire-mock-target="overlay"
         class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-10 hidden items-center justify-center bg-white/70 backdrop-blur-sm dark:bg-gray-950/70">
      <div data-retire-mock-target="bubble"
           class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-300 bg-white px-8 py-6 text-center shadow-sm dark:border-emerald-700 dark:bg-gray-900">
        <p class="text-3xl">🎓</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">Retired</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-lg font-medium">“<%= @sample[:just_retired][:word] %>”</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
          You'll recall this ~6 months out. It's leaving your rotation —
          you've earned the space.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <button type="button" data-action="retire-mock#play"
          class="mt-4 rounded-md border border-gray-300 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:border-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
    ▶ Replay the moment
  </button>
  <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-gray-400">Auto-dismisses; the drill flows straight on to the next card.</p>
</section>

<%# ============================================================ %>
<%# 2. THE SHELF — where retired words land (the home for the moment)    %>
<%# ============================================================ %>
<section class="mb-14">
  <div class="mb-3 flex items-baseline justify-between">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-400">Retired words</p>
    <p class="text-[11px] tabular-nums text-gray-400"><%= @sample[:shelf].size %> mastered</p>
  </div>

  <%# A quiet shelf: one line each, hairline dividers, emerald cap (🎓) as the
      only accent. The celebrated thing has somewhere to live — not a dead flash. %>
  <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-100 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-800 dark:border-gray-800">
    <% @sample[:shelf].each do |w| %>
      <li class="flex items-center justify-between px-3 py-2">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-500 dark:text-emerald-400">🎓</span>
          <span class="font-medium"><%= w[:word] %></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400"><%= w[:gloss] %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 text-[11px] tabular-nums text-gray-400">
          <span>recall ~<%= (w[:stability_days] / 30.0).round %> mo</span>
          <span>retired <%= w[:retired_on] %></span>
        </div>
      </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-gray-400">
    Tap any word to un-retire it if it slips — retiring is a celebration, not a lock.
  </p>
</section>

<%# ============================================================ %>
<%# 3. APPROACHING — the "almost there" affordance (a quiet hint)        %>
<%# ============================================================ %>
<section class="mb-14">
  <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-400">Almost there</p>
  <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
    A faint sense of nearing the finish — never a loud progress bar competing
    with the word. A thin emerald sliver under the row, nothing more.
  </p>

  <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
    <% @sample[:approaching].each do |w| %>
      <% pct = [(w[:stability_days].to_f / @retire_threshold * 100).round, 100].min %>
      <li class="px-1 py-2">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
          <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
            <span class="font-medium"><%= w[:word] %></span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400"><%= w[:gloss] %></span>
          </div>
          <span class="text-[11px] tabular-nums text-gray-400"><%= pct %>% to retired</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-1.5 h-0.5 w-full rounded-full bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
          <div class="h-0.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400/70 dark:bg-emerald-500/60" style="width: <%= pct %>%"></div>
        </div>
      </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
</section>

<%# ============================================================ %>
<%# Rounds — keep rejected directions visible so we don't re-propose them %>
<%# ============================================================ %>
<details class="mt-16 border-t border-gray-200 pt-4 dark:border-gray-800">
  <summary class="cursor-pointer text-xs text-gray-400">Round 1 — directions considered &amp; set aside</summary>
  <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
    <li>· <span class="line-through">Full-screen confetti burst</span> — too loud; this app's celebrate language is a quiet pop, not a party.</li>
    <li>· <span class="line-through">Silent retire (LingQ-style)</span> — that's the gap we're filling; the whole point is to mark the moment.</li>
    <li>· <span class="line-through">A loud progress bar on every drilling word</span> — competes with the word; reduced to a thin sliver only on words actually nearing retirement.</li>
    <li>· <span class="line-through">Retired words just disappear</span> — a celebrated thing needs a home; added the shelf so the moment has somewhere to land.</li>
  </ul>
</details>
